1. Ubuntu EC2 machine.
Open required ports (22, 8080, 3000, 9090, 80, 443) in the Security Group
2. Putty
[dnf for amazon machine, else use apt or yum for other machines]
3. In system 
    ğŸ”¹ Step 1: Update System
        sudo dnf update -y
    ğŸ”¹ Step 2: Install Java (Required for Jenkins)
        sudo dnf install -y java-17-amazon-corretto
    ğŸ”¹ Step 3: Add Jenkins Repository (cuz Amazon Linux 2023 does not have Jenkins by default, manually add the repository)
        sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
        Then import the GPG key:
        sudo rpm --import https://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
    ğŸ”¹ Step 4: Install Jenkins
        sudo dnf install -y jenkins
    ğŸ”¹ Step 5: Start and Enable Jenkins Service
        sudo systemctl enable jenkins
        sudo systemctl start jenkins
        Check the status to ensure Jenkins is running:
        sudo systemctl status jenkins
    ğŸ”¹ Step 6: Open Port 8080 in Firewall
        sudo firewall-cmd --add-port=8080/tcp --permanent
        sudo firewall-cmd --reload
    ğŸ”¹ Step 7: Get Initial Admin Password
        sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
    ğŸ”¹ Step 8: Access Jenkins Web UI
        http://<EC2-Public-IP>:8080  [IP of EC2 instance]



